                                                                                                                       7                                        Title for Paes-Black
                  Leander Paes and Cara Black at Wimbledon, on Sunday                     
	London: Leander Paes and Cara Black won the mixed doubles title at Wimbledon defeating Wesley Moodie and Lisa Raymond 6-4, 7-6 (5) on Sunday.         
	The Indo-Zimbabwean pair, who were the runner-up last year, took just 37 minutes to win the first set featuring five breaks of serve, including one for every player in the first five games.         
	The second set was tighter with the match going with serve, although Black and Raymond each struggled in one game.         
	Paes and Black trailed 4-2 in the second-set tiebreaker but won five of the next six points.         
	Paes sealed victory with a volley at the net.         
	Paes and Black had each won the Wimbledon title before with different partners.         
	Paes has lifted the trophy twice previously  with Martina Navratilova in 2003 and Lisa Raymond in 1999  while Black won it with brother Wayne in 2004.         
	This was Paes and Blacks third Slam together. They had earlier won the Australian Open in January this year and the US Open in 2008.         
	This was Leanders 12th Slam making him the Indian with the highest number of majors. His former partner Mahesh Bhupathi has 11 Slams to his name.  
